<bibRefCitation id="EFC15DAFC3025A72FE1CF875FC9BF84B" author="Barbosa MA &amp; Costa WJEM" box="[502,768,1999,2023]" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" pagination="175 - 186" refId="ref6281" refString="Barbosa MA, Costa WJEM (2008) Description of a new species of catfish from the upper rio Paraiba do Sul basin, south-eastern Brazil (Teleostei: Siluriformes: Trichomycteridae) and re-description of Trichomycterus itatiayae. aqua, International Journal of Ichthyology 14 (4): 175 - 186." type="journal article" year="2008">Barbosa &amp; Costa, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<figureCitation id="136B3CDBC3025A72FF42F84BFE8AF7A5" box="[168,273,2033,2057]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,998,1018]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,160,973]" captionTargetId="figure-466@5.[168,1423,160,973]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Fish species collected in upper Piraí river drainage. A. Trichomycterus macrophthalmus, MNRJ 43760, 52.4 mm SL. B. Imparfinis minutus, MNRJ 43770, 83.4 mm SL. C. Trichomycterus mariamole, MNRJ 36525, 58.72 mm SL. D. Pimelodella lateristriga, MNRJ 43888, 39.7 mm SL. E. Trichomycterus nigroauratus, MNRJ 38003, 48.8 mm SL. F. Rhamdia quelen, MNRJ 43889, 98.6 mm SL. G. Scleromystax barbatus, MNRJ 46722, 66.1 mm SL, male. H. Scleromystax barbatus, MNRJ 46722, 57.62 mm SL, female." pageId="5" pageNumber="240">Figure 3E</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF205EC3025A72FF24F7A9FC9DF787" blockId="5.[168,774,1999,2091]" box="[206,774,2067,2091]" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">Geographic distribution: Upper Piraí and Barreiro</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A73D5C3025A72FCC7FB3BFB3DFA5F" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF205EC3025A72FCC7FB3BFAACFB35" blockId="5.[813,1420,1153,1523]" box="[813,1335,1153,1177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">
river drainages in the 
<collectingRegion id="4994EEBCC3025A72FBF3FB3BFBF1FB35" box="[1049,1130,1153,1177]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
do Sul river basin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF205EC3025A72FCB8FB1EFB3DFA5F" blockId="5.[813,1420,1153,1523]" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3025A72FC21FB1EFA93FB10" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Costa" authorityYear="2008" box="[971,1288,1188,1212]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigroauratus">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3025A72FC21FB1EFA93FB10" box="[971,1288,1188,1212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">Trichomycterus nigroauratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs morphologically from 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3025A72FC1FFB7DFB1EFB72" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Costa" authorityYear="2010" box="[1013,1157,1222,1246]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mariamole">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3025A72FC1FFB7DFB1EFB72" box="[1013,1157,1222,1246]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">T. mariamole</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3025A72FB51FB7DFA17FB72" box="[1211,1420,1222,1246]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrophthalmus">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3025A72FB51FB7DFA17FB72" box="[1211,1420,1222,1246]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">T. macrophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of golden spots on the snout and body, and broad (wider than long) metapterygoid bone (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC15DAFC3025A72FAB1FAB6FBB0FAEA" author="Barbosa MA &amp; Costa WJEM" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" pagination="175 - 186" refId="ref6281" refString="Barbosa MA, Costa WJEM (2008) Description of a new species of catfish from the upper rio Paraiba do Sul basin, south-eastern Brazil (Teleostei: Siluriformes: Trichomycteridae) and re-description of Trichomycterus itatiayae. aqua, International Journal of Ichthyology 14 (4): 175 - 186." type="journal article" year="2008">Barbosa and Costa 2008</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C505BDDC3025A72FBAFFA94FA17FAEA" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Costa" authorityYear="2008" box="[1093,1420,1326,1350]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigroauratus">
<emphasis id="B924FC4CC3025A72FBAFFA94FA17FAEA" box="[1093,1420,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="240">Trichomycterus nigroauratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents ontogenetic variation of coloration, with juveniles exhibiting a black stripe along the lateral midline, and adults presenting stripes with irregular borders and dark stains that can cover the entire body in a homogeneous pattern (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC15DAFC3025A72FC27FA60FB01FA5F" author="Buckup PA &amp; Britto MR &amp; Souza-Lima R. &amp; Pascoli JC &amp; Villa-Verde L &amp; Ferraro GA &amp; Salgado FLK &amp; Gomes JR" box="[973,1178,1498,1523]" pageId="5" pageNumber="240" refId="ref6473" refString="Buckup PA, Britto MR, Souza-Lima R., Pascoli JC, Villa-Verde L, Ferraro GA, Salgado FLK, Gomes JR (2014) Guia de Identificacao das Especies de Peixes da Bacia do Rio das Pedras Municipio de Rio Claro, RJ. The Nature Conservancy, Rio de Janeiro, 144 pp." type="book" year="2014">Buckup et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
